        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>POSTAL CARD<lb/>
            WRITE THE ADDRESS ON THIS SIDE&#8212;THE MESSAGE ON THE OTHER<lb/></p>
            
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
            North Fifth Street below Green<lb/>
            Philadelphia<lb/>
            Pa.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>April 2. 77<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. &#38; Dear Sir&#8212;You must excuse my long silence<lb/> as I had not a minute&#39;s time to devote to our correspondence&#44;<lb/> you will read the cause in next week&#39;s J. R. Please the<lb/> Lord&#44; after P. I will do better.  The object of this hurried card<lb/> is this&#58; I sent you my sermon of 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> P. for criticism.  I know<lb/> you take an interest in my welfare.  Send me your opinion&#44;<lb/> criticize if it needs it&#44; or the contrary if not.  My friends<lb/> differ as to the merits of this lecture &#38; since your<lb/> opinion is of the greatest value to me&#44; I wish to<lb/> know whether you approve of all sentiments&#44; &#38; ideas<lb/> embodied therein	Ever yours<lb/></p>
            									<p>Jacob Voorsanger<lb/></p>
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#93;</p>
        </body>
    </text>
